"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715045","Department for Education","false","2017-04-27","<p>The Government values the contribution that international students make to higher education, research, and the UK, both economically and culturally. That is why we have no plans to introduce a cap on the number of genuine international students who can come here to study, or to limit the numbers that individual higher education institutions can recruit. The reforms the Government is introducing through the Higher Education and Research Bill recognise the importance of the sector to the economy and will help to ensure that it continues to be one of the most sought after places for global talent to study.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2017-04-27T08:09:29.437Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715045/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715045/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715045/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-03-29","Universities: Overseas Students","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what assessment she has made of the implications for universities of the Universities UK report, entitled The economic impact of international students, published in March 2017.","false","Biography information for Martyn Day","Linlithgow and East Falkirk","Martyn Day","69668"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715046","Department for Education","false","2017-04-19","<p>The Higher Education Statistics Agency (HESA) collects and publishes statistics on students enrolled at UK higher education institutions (HEIs). The latest available statistics refer to the 2015/16 academic year and are published at the following link:</p><p><a href="https://www.hesa.ac.uk/news/12-01-2017/sfr242-student-enrolments-and-qualifications" target="_blank">https://www.hesa.ac.uk/news/12-01-2017/sfr242-student-enrolments-and-qualifications</a></p><p> </p><p>The proportion of higher education enrolments that were female, by mode and location of study has been provided for the academic years 2006/07 to 2015/16 in the attached table.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2017-04-19T13:23:58.893Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715046/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715046/answer","69700 - table.pdf","69700 - table.pdf","69700 - table","69700 - table","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715046/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-03-29","Higher Education: Females","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what proportion of students undertaking (a) full-time and (b) part-time courses at higher education institutions in (i) Scotland, (ii) England, (iii) Wales, (iv) Northern Ireland and (v) the UK were women in each of the last 10 years.","false","Biography information for Alison Thewliss","Glasgow Central","Alison Thewliss","69700"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715047","Department for Education","false","2017-04-19","<p>The Higher Education Statistics Agency (HESA) collects and publishes data on students enrolled at UK Higher Education Institutions (HEIs). The latest available statistics refer to the 2015/16 academic year and are published at the following link:</p><p><a href="https://www.hesa.ac.uk/news/12-01-2017/sfr242-student-enrolments-and-qualifications" target="_blank">https://www.hesa.ac.uk/news/12-01-2017/sfr242-student-enrolments-and-qualifications</a></p><p> </p><p>Statistics on enrolments in part-time study by gender and level of study in the latest ten years for which data are available have been provided in the attached table.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2017-04-19T13:24:43.437Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715047/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715047/answer","69698 table.pdf","69698 table.pdf","69698 table","69698 table","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715047/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-03-29","Part-time Education","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many (a) female and (b) male students have undertaken part-time (i) undergraduate and (ii) postgraduate courses in the UK in each of the last 10 years.","false","Biography information for Alison Thewliss","Glasgow Central","Alison Thewliss","69698"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715048","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-04-18","<p>No such reports have been commissioned or published in the last 12 months.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2017-04-18T10:40:06.227Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715048/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715048/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715048/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-03-29","Bovine Tuberculosis: Vaccination","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, whether her Department has commissioned or published any reports on vaccination as an alternative option to culling in the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","69714"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715049","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-04-18","<p>It is the responsibility of individual horse owners to ensure that their horses are identified and registered on the Central Equine Database. Local Authorities are responsible for enforcing these requirements.</p><p>Defra launched a consultation on 5 April 2017 to implement requirements relating to the identification and registration of equines and the new Central Equine Database. It is published at:</p><p><a href="https://consult.defra.gov.uk/equine-id/revised-eu-rules-on-equine-id-eu-reg-eu-2015-262" target="_blank">https://consult.defra.gov.uk/equine-id/revised-eu-rules-on-equine-id-eu-reg-eu-2015-262</a></p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2017-04-18T11:28:14.297Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715049/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715049/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715049/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-03-29","Horses: Databases","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, pursuant to the Answer of 27 February 2017 to Question 64423, what steps her Department plans to take to enforce compliance with the requirement that owners of horses and ponies register on the central equine database; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Lord Garnier","Harborough","Sir Edward Garnier","69673"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715050","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-04-18","<p>The information requested is not collated centrally and could only be provided at disproportionate cost.</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2017-04-18T10:48:02.81Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715050/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715050/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715050/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-03-29","Fisheries: Employment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what estimate she has made of the number of jobs in the fishing industry which have been directly funded through the European Maritime and Fisheries Fund in each of the last 10 years; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","69697"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715051","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-04-18","<p>The average amount of compensation paid, per animal, to dairy farmers whose cattle have been compulsory slaughtered for bovine TB for the last five years is shown in the table below. These include all reactors and contacts. It is rarely necessary to slaughter an entire herd.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Year</p></td><td><p>Average Value</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012</p></td><td><p>£1,205.33</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013</p></td><td><p>£1,181.03</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014</p></td><td><p>£1,151.47</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015</p></td><td><p>£1,066.74</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2016</p></td><td><p>£936.54</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>The values in the table are for England only. Both the Scottish and Welsh Governments pay and record compensation payments separately to farmers who have had their animal’s compulsory slaughtered for bovine TB.</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2017-04-18T11:01:13.61Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715051/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715051/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715051/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-03-29","Bovine Tuberculosis: Disease Control","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what the average amount of compensation paid, per animal, to dairy farmers whose herds have been compulsorily slaughtered for bovine TB has been in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Sue Hayman","Workington","Sue Hayman","69754"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715052","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-04-18","<p>The most recent UK Production to Supply Ratio is 61% for all food and 76% for indigenous type food.</p><p> </p><p>We do not predict future ratios given the uncertainty over the many dependent factors including global food commodity prices, exchange rates, climate and weather, as well as discrete factors such as plant and animal disease. However, the Government has a policy of supporting our food and farming industry so that we can grow more and sell more British produce.</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2017-04-18T11:23:05.193Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715052/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715052/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715052/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-03-29","Food Supply","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what assessment her Department has made of potential trends in the level of food self-sufficiency in each of the next 10 years; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","69694"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715053","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-04-18","<p>Since 8 May 2015 two official documents and 12 official sensitive documents have been recorded as lost by Defra.</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2017-04-18T16:01:01.203Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715053/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715053/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715053/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-03-29","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs: Data Protection","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, how many (a) official and (b) official sensitive documents have been recorded as lost by her Department since 8 May 2015.","false","Biography information for Tim Farron","Westmorland and Lonsdale","Tim Farron","69812"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715054","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-04-18","<p>The Government annually publishes Family Food, which draws on data from the Living Cost of Food Survey. This publication includes questions on household spend on food, including that by the lowest 20% income households, which has remained constant at around 16% for a number of years.</p><p>The Food Insecurity Experience Scale (FIES), developed by the Voices of the Hungry project of the UN Food and Agriculture Organisation (FAO) is used to collect food security data in up to 150 countries under the Gallup World Poll. The Department for International Development supports this work financially and updated results will be published later this year by the FAO. We understand from the FAO that global FIES results will be launched in June, and the individual country level estimates, which are three-year averages, will be published in September.</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2017-04-18T11:57:52.963Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715054/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715054/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715054/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-03-29","Food Poverty","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what recent estimate her Department has made of the level of household food insecurity in the UK; and pursuant to the Answer of 12 September 2016 by the Minister of State for Health to Question 44475, when the Government expects the data provided to the Voices of the Hungry project to be published.","false","Biography information for Mrs Emma Lewell-Buck","South Shields","Mrs Emma Lewell-Buck","69890"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715055","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-04-24","<p>HM Revenue and Customs have a budget of £20 million to enforce the National Minimum Wage for 2016/17, up from £13m in 2015/16.</p><p>In the 2016 Autumn Statement my right hon. Friend the Chancellor of the Exchequer announced a £4.3m increase, further to the £1 million already planned, bringing the enforcement budget to £25.3 million for 2017/18.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2017-04-24T09:09:13.573Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715055/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715055/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715055/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-03-29","Minimum Wage: Enforcement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what the budget is for HM Revenue and Customs national minimum wage enforcement for 2016-17.","false","Biography information for Paul Blomfield","Sheffield Central","Paul Blomfield","69835"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715056","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-04-18","<p>The Department has published research on the main drivers of changes to food prices which have been observed to be food commodity prices, currency exchange rates and oil prices. It will be changes to any, or a combination of these factors, that will bring changes to prices.</p><p>ONS statistics on food prices are published each month as part of the Consumer Price Index. In the most recent statistics published on 11 April, food prices had increased by 1.3% in the year to March 2017 following almost three consecutive years where food prices fell. Exchange rates and energy costs have been the key drivers of these changes.</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2017-04-18T11:42:22.387Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715056/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715056/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715056/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-03-29","Food: Prices","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what change her Department expects in the level of food prices in the next six months.","false","Biography information for Mrs Emma Lewell-Buck","South Shields","Mrs Emma Lewell-Buck","69859"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715057","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-04-20","<p>We discuss nuclear non-proliferation and disarmament frequently with a wide range of partners, amongst them states attending these negotiations. In such discussions we have been clear about our opposition to this move to negotiate a treaty banning nuclear weapons for the reasons we have set out to this House. The first Preparatory Committee for the 2020 Nuclear Non-Proliferation Treaty Review Conference will take place in Vienna in May and we will use that forum to engage with a wide range of states on how we can together tackle the challenges we face on non-proliferation and disarmament, and enable access to the peaceful use of nuclear technology.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2017-04-20T16:39:26.203Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715057/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715057/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715057/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-03-29","Nuclear Disarmament","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, pursuant to the Answer of 13 March 2017 to Question 66495, what steps he plans to take to communicate with the participants at the organisational meeting on negotiating a treaty to prohibit nuclear weapons on 16 February 2017, and the substantive negotiations starting on 27 March 2017 on that subject; and whether he plans to make a statement after the conclusion of those negotiations.","false","Biography information for Richard Fuller","Bedford","Richard Fuller","69875"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715058","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-04-19","<p>The UK supports the UN Group of Experts in their investigations into the causes and drivers of conflict in the Democratic Republic of Congo (DRC), including human rights violations in the Kasai provinces. I made a statement on 29 March expressing my sincere condolences for the deaths of two of their members in the region. The UN Security Council has called on the Government of the DRC to swiftly investigate these crimes and bring the perpetrators to justice. We welcome the UN inquiry into the events and their commitment to do everything possible to ensure that justice is done.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2017-04-19T13:43:49.373Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715058/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715058/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715058/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-03-29","Democratic Republic of Congo: Human Rights","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, if the Government will take steps at the UN Security Council or the UN Human Rights Council to support the creation of an international investigation into human rights violations in the Kasai provinces of the Democratic Republic of Congo.","false","Biography information for Lord Mann","Bassetlaw","John Mann","69892"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715059","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-04-19","<p>The recent renewal of the MONUSCO mandate on 31 March focussed the mission on the protection of civilians and supporting the implementation of the 31 December political agreement, including elections. The UK successfully shaped Security Council negotiations to ensure the mission has the necessary resources to fulfil its core mandate.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2017-04-19T13:47:16.37Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715059/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715059/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715059/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-03-29","Democratic Republic of Congo: Elections","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, if he will take steps to promote provision of resources to the UN Organisation Stabilisation Mission in the Democratic Republic of Congo sufficient to protect civilians and support the organisation of free, fair and credible elections in 2017 in that country.","false","Biography information for Lord Mann","Bassetlaw","John Mann","69893"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715060","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-04-21","<p>Materials designated Official or Official-Sensitive do have a level of protection, however loss of its control does not warrant a breach as per existing Cabinet Office guidelines. Figures for all loss at this classification is not recorded centrally.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2017-04-21T11:48:20.293Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715060/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715060/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715060/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-03-29","Foreign and Commonwealth Office: Data Protection","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, how many (a) official and (b) official sensitive documents have been recorded as lost by his Department since 8 May 2015.","false","Biography information for Tim Farron","Westmorland and Lonsdale","Tim Farron","69820"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715061","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-04-20","<p>The Foreign and Commonwealth Office refers to the guidelines and procedures governing the acceptance, classification, recording, retention and disposal of gifts by Members of The Royal Family set out by Buckingham Palace and published on the Royal.uk website, and where appropriate consults the government of the country concerned.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2017-04-20T16:40:08.113Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715061/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715061/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715061/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-03-29","Monarchy: Official Gifts","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what criteria his Department uses in advice to the Royal Family on the suitability of accepting gifts.","false","Biography information for Mr Virendra Sharma","Ealing, Southall","Mr Virendra Sharma","69713"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715062","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-04-24","<p>The Foreign and Commonwealth Office highlights the risks of carbon monoxide poisoning on our Foreign Travel Checklist on the GOV.UK website, and provides links to the 'Be Alarmed' (<a href="http://www.co-bealarmed.co.uk/" target="_blank">http://www.co-bealarmed.co.uk</a>) national campaign, which includes guidance on staying safe and recommends taking a portable carbon monoxide alarm when travelling.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2017-04-24T13:28:33.173Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715062/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715062/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715062/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-03-29","British Nationals Abroad: Carbon Monoxide","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, if he will maker it his policy to encourage travellers to bring a carbon monoxide alarm with them when travelling abroad.","false","Biography information for Mr Barry Sheerman","Huddersfield","Mr Barry Sheerman","69708"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715063","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-04-24","<p>I am not aware of any fundamental concerns with the UK police force's extraterritorial jurisdiction. Issues relating to individual cases are treated on a case-by-case basis</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2017-04-24T15:31:51.573Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715063/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715063/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715063/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-03-29","Crimes Outside National Territories: British Nationals Abroad","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what steps his Department has taken to assess the effectiveness of extraterritorial jurisdiction in allowing the UK police force to investigate crimes committed against UK citizens abroad.","false","Biography information for Kate Osamor","Edmonton","Kate Osamor","69726"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715064","Department for International Development","false","2017-04-24","<p>Discussions with Commonwealth members and other countries on global health threats including malaria take place through a number of international bodies, for example the World Health Organization, the UN General Assembly, and the Global Fund to Fight AIDS, Tuberculosis, and Malaria.</p><p>The Secretary of State for International Development has visited Commonwealth countries including India, Pakistan, and Sierra Leone since taking office, and has used these visits to discuss a range of critical issues, including health and development.</p>","Stockton South","James Wharton",,"2017-04-24T15:33:25.547Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715064/answer","Biography information for James Wharton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715064/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715064/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-03-29","Commonwealth: Health","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what recent discussions she has had with her Commonwealth counterparts on tackling (a) malaria and (b) other global health threats.","false","Biography information for David Mackintosh","Northampton South","David Mackintosh","69752"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715065","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-04-20","<p>None.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2017-04-20T16:40:42.823Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715065/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715065/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715065/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-03-29","Monarchy: Official Gifts","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what discussions his Department has had with representatives of the Order of the Eagle of Georgia and the Seamless Tunic of Our Lord Jesus Christ on the gift of a gold chain from the alleged Crown Prince Davit of Georgia.","false","Biography information for Mr Virendra Sharma","Ealing, Southall","Mr Virendra Sharma","69705"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715066","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-04-24","<p>While the number of consular cases involving British nationals affected by carbon monoxide poisoning overseas is very low, carbon monoxide safety and awareness remains important. We work with the travel industry through our 'Travel Aware' travel safety campaign to highlight safety risks to British nationals abroad. We also highlight the risks of carbon monoxide poisoning on our Foreign Travel Checklist on the GOV.UK website, and link to the 'Be Alarmed' (<a href="http://www.co-bealarmed.co.uk/" target="_blank">http://www.co-bealarmed.co.uk</a>) national campaign, whose website includes advice on how to stay safe for those travelling abroad.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2017-04-24T13:26:47.41Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715066/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715066/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715066/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-03-29","British Nationals Abroad: Carbon Monoxide","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, if he will set out the Government's position on the promotion of carbon monoxide safety for people travelling abroad.","false","Biography information for Mr Barry Sheerman","Huddersfield","Mr Barry Sheerman","69707"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715067","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-04-19","<p>While the UK Government welcomes the spirit of the Safe Schools Declaration, we remain concerned that the accompanying Guidelines for Protecting Schools and Universities from Military use during Armed Conflict do not mirror the exact language of International Humanitarian Law.</p><p>Under International Humanitarian Law, the UK already affords schools and educational establishments a high degree of protection during military operations. We take these international obligations very seriously and believe better implementation of, and compliance with, International Humanitarian Law by all parties to armed conflict provides the best protection for civilians, including children. For this reason, the UK Government has not signed the declaration.</p><p>The UK Government will, however, continue to keep this policy under review.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2017-04-19T16:00:24.973Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715067/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715067/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715067/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-03-29","Armed Conflict: Schools","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, if he will make it his policy to sign the Safe Schools Declaration.","false","Biography information for Sarah Olney","Richmond Park","Sarah Olney","69669"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715068","Home Office","false","2017-04-18","<p>We operate several resettlement schemes, working closely with the United Nations High Commissioner for Refugees to provide a safe and legal route to the UK for the most vulnerable refugees. Medical needs is one of the vulnerability criteria used to identify refugees for resettlement to the UK.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-04-18T15:31:52.67Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715068/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715068/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715068/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-03-29","Refugees: Health Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what the Government's policy is on facilitating access to the UK for refugees who are in urgent need of healthcare for life-threatening conditions.","false","Biography information for Mr Roger Godsiff","Birmingham, Hall Green","Mr Roger Godsiff","69667"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715069","Department of Health","false","2017-04-18","<p>My Rt. hon. Friend the Secretary of State for Health is not a member of the Government’s European Union Exit and Trade Committee as under article 168, section 7, of the Lisbon Treaty, health is a member state competence, so he does not need to attend every session. He is invited every time a matter directly affecting health comes up.</p><p> </p><p>The list of Cabinet Committees and Implementation Taskforces, and their membership, is published here:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/the-cabinet-committees-system-and-list-of-cabinet-committees" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/the-cabinet-committees-system-and-list-of-cabinet-committees</a></p><p> </p><p>Other Ministers attend the European Union Exit and Trade Committee where the agenda item concerns their portfolio.</p>","Warrington South","David Mowat",,"2017-04-18T14:13:34.067Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715069/answer","Biography information for David Mowat","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715069/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715069/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-03-29","Department of Health: EU Exit and Trade Committee","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, for what reason he is not a member of the Government's European Union Exit and Trade Committee.","false","Biography information for Tracy Brabin","Batley and Spen","Tracy Brabin","69662"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715070","Department of Health","false","2017-04-19","<p>The Department of Health part funded the Cannabinoid Use in Progressive Inflammatory brain Disease study through the National Institute for Health Research’s (NIHR) Health Technology Assessment programme. The report of this study was published in February 2015 and is available on the NIHR Journals Library website at:</p><p><a href="http://www.journalslibrary.nihr.ac.uk/hta/volume-19/issue-12#abstract" target="_blank">http://www.journalslibrary.nihr.ac.uk/hta/volume-19/issue-12#abstract</a></p>","Oxford West and Abingdon","Nicola Blackwood",,"2017-04-19T08:40:08.85Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715070/answer","Biography information for Baroness Blackwood of North Oxford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715070/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715070/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-03-29","Cannabis","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, whether his Department has commissioned or published reports on the use of medicinal cannabis.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","69721"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715071","Department of Health","false","2017-04-18","<p>On 4 October 2016 my Rt. hon. Friend the Secretary of State for Health announced that the number of medical training places available to students each year will be expanded by 1,500 (25%) to ensure the National Health Service in England has the future supply of doctors it needs to continue to provide safe, compassionate care. In September 2018, the Government will fund 500 additional student places through medical schools in England each year. The Government is currently consulting on how to make available the further 1,000 places from 2019/20 to medical schools in England.</p><p> </p><p>Health Education England is responsible for ensuring that there is sufficient future supply of staff to meet the workforce requirements of the English health system. Information on future supply and specialty fill rates can be found in Health Education England’s Workforce Plan for England, available at:</p><p><a href="https://www.hee.nhs.uk/sites/default/files/documents/HEE%20commissioning%20and%20investment%20plan%202016-17_0.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.hee.nhs.uk/sites/default/files/documents/HEE%20commissioning%20and%20investment%20plan%202016-17_0.pdf</a></p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2017-04-18T10:29:23.95Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715071/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715071/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715071/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-03-29","Junior Doctors: Training","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what steps he is taking to ensure that adequate numbers of junior doctors are being trained.","false","Biography information for Ian Lavery","Wansbeck","Ian Lavery","69736"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715072","Department of Health","false","2017-04-18","<p>In accordance with NHS England guidance and accounting rules, details of the salaries of Executive, general practitioner and lay members of the Clinical Commissioning Group Governing Body are published annually and follow the nationally prescribed format in the Remuneration Report. This forms part of the Annual Report of the clinical commissioning group which is publically available from the clinical commissioning group website and by request.</p><p> </p><p>Remuneration is set by the Remuneration Committee of the Clinical Commissioning Group in accordance with the Clinical Commissioning Group Constitution and NHS England guidance.</p><p> </p><p>The Department has asked NHS England to look into the remuneration of governing body members at the Liverpool Clinical Commissioning Group.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2017-04-18T10:47:52.123Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715072/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715072/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715072/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-03-29","Liverpool Clinical Commissioning Group: Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what the assurance process used by NHS England was to ensure governance, probity and value for money in the award of salary increases to the Liverpool Clinical Commissioning Group governing body members in 2014-15.","false","Biography information for Rosie Cooper","West Lancashire","Rosie Cooper","69749"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715073","Department of Health","false","2017-04-18","<p>The Department of Health NHS Choice Framework identifies the choices patients have. In some circumstances they have legal rights to choice and must be given these choices by law. In other circumstances there is no guaranteed right to choice however, depending on what is available locally, patients should be offered choice where possible.</p><p> </p><p>If a person needs to be referred as an outpatient to see a consultant or specialist they may choose the organisation that provides their National Health Service care and treatment. They may choose whenever they are referred for the first time for an appointment for a physical or mental health condition, as appropriate. They may choose any organisation that provides clinically appropriate care for their condition that has been appointed by the NHS to provide that service. There are circumstances in which they may not choose, these are also set out in the document.</p><p> </p><p>Individuals can talk to their general practitioner, dentist, optometrist or other person who is referring them for more information. They can also find out more information on the NHS Choices website about the organisations they can choose from, a link to which can be found here:</p><p><a href="http://www.nhs.uk/pages/home.aspx" target="_blank">http://www.nhs.uk/pages/home.aspx</a></p><p> </p><p>This is a national website for patients.</p><p> </p><p>Additionally, commissioners have obligations to procure health care services from providers best placed to meet the needs of patients. If commissioners have concerns about the quality of health care services provided by any of its current providers then they may decide to procure services from alternative providers. More information about these obligations can be found at the following address:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/procurement-patient-choice-and-competition-regulations-guidance" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/procurement-patient-choice-and-competition-regulations-guidance</a></p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","69758 ; 69760","2017-04-18T10:27:30.483Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715073/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715073/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715073/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-03-29","Clinical Commissioning Groups: Contracts","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what steps he is taking to ensure the best quality of care for patients in circumstances where a clinical commissioning group commissions a service from only one provider and that provider has been assessed by the Care Quality Commission as requiring improvement.","false","Biography information for Helen Jones","Warrington North","Helen Jones","69757"
