"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715076","Department of Health","false","2017-04-18","<p>NHS Digital publishes quarterly data on turnover by nationality of staff working in the National Health Service in England. In addition, NHS Digital publishes staff in post figures bi annually.</p><p> </p><p>Nationality is self-reported within the NHS human resources and payroll system, the electronic staff record.</p><p> </p><p>The information is shown in the attached tables. The December data is the most recent data available.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2017-04-18T16:35:58.25Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715076/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715076/answer","PQ69764 attached document.xlsx","PQ69764 attached document.xlsx","PQ69764 attached tables","PQ69764 attached tables","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715076/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-03-29","Health Professions: Labour Turnover","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many (a) nurses, (b) doctors and (c) other NHS staff have left employment in (i) 2014, (ii) 2015 and (iii) 2016; and how many people in each such category were non-UK EU or EEA nationals.","false","Biography information for Tim Farron","Westmorland and Lonsdale","Tim Farron","69764"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715077","Department of Health","false","2017-04-24","<p>The Department has had two reported data-related incidents since 8 May 2015 that involved the loss of electronic or physical documents.</p>","Warrington South","David Mowat",,"2017-04-24T11:18:42.873Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715077/answer","Biography information for David Mowat","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715077/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715077/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-03-29","Department of Health: Data Protection","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many (a) official and (b) official sensitive documents have been recorded as lost by his Department since 8 May 2015.","false","Biography information for Tim Farron","Westmorland and Lonsdale","Tim Farron","69825"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715078","Department of Health","false","2017-04-18","<p>NHS Digital publishes quarterly data on turnover by nationality of staff working in the National Health Service in England. In addition, NHS Digital publishes staff in post figures bi annually.</p><p> </p><p>Nationality is self-reported within the NHS human resources and payroll system, the electronic staff record.</p><p> </p><p>Social Care Workers have been defined as all staff within the Social Services care setting of the NHS occupation codes.</p><p> </p><p>The information is shown in the attached tables. The December data is the most recent data available.</p>","Warrington South","David Mowat",,"2017-04-18T10:59:38.533Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715078/answer","Biography information for David Mowat","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715078/answer","PQ69902 tables.xlsx","PQ69902 tables.xlsx","PQ69902 attached tables","PQ69902 attached tables","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715078/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-03-29","Social Services: Labour Turnover","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many social care workers left employment with the NHS in (a) 2014, (b) 2015 and (c) 2016; and how many such workers were non-UK EU or EEA nationals.","false","Biography information for Tim Farron","Westmorland and Lonsdale","Tim Farron","69902"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715079","Department of Health","false","2017-04-24","<p>The figures for take-up of the Healthy Start scheme for 2015-16 and 2016-17 are as follows:</p><p> </p><p>- Between 6 April 2015 and 3 April 2016, 197,842 eligible beneficiaries were invited to apply. 208,486 applications were received, of which 147,124 were approved as meeting the criteria (74%).</p><p>- Between 4 April 2016 and 5 March 2017, 198,319 eligible beneficiaries were invited to apply. 172,020 applications were received, of which 125,134 were approved as meeting the criteria (63%).</p><p> </p><p>Expenditure on the Healthy Start Scheme is demand-led and based on the number of eligible people who apply for it. The Government is working to ensure that eligible families are aware of the scheme and how it can help them. It is promoted via the Healthy Start and Start4Life websites, reminding families to take up the vouchers. We are also exploring how digital technology could make it easier for people to receive Healthy Start benefits in the future, as part of the Government’s wider digital strategy. At a local level, midwives and health visitors play a key role in promoting awareness of the scheme.</p>","Oxford West and Abingdon","Nicola Blackwood",,"2017-04-24T12:37:39.907Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715079/answer","Biography information for Baroness Blackwood of North Oxford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715079/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715079/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-03-29","Healthy Start Scheme","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many and what proportion of eligible people applied for the Healthy Start scheme in (a) 2015-16 and (b) 2016-17 to date; and what plans his Department has to increase uptake of that scheme.","false","Biography information for Mrs Emma Lewell-Buck","South Shields","Mrs Emma Lewell-Buck","69891"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715080","Home Office","false","2017-04-24","<p>These matters are the responsibility of the Cabinet Office and the Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs. They deal with complex supply chains and flooding respectively.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2017-04-24T15:34:42.683Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715080/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715080/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715080/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-03-29","Aviation: Natural Disasters","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what plans she has to use general aviation airfields and volunteer pilots to enhance emergency supply chains during natural disasters such as floods.","false","Biography information for Lord Davies of Gower","Gower","Byron Davies","69871"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715081","Home Office","false","2017-04-18","<p>The following organisations will receive funding under the Modern Slavery Innovation Fund round that concluded in March 2017: The Salvation Army, The Freedom Fund, Retrak, Pacific Links Foundation, NSPCC, Alliance HR, GoodWeave International, St Mary’s University, University of Bedfordshire and United Nations University.</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton",,"2017-04-18T16:46:43.457Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715081/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715081/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715081/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-03-29","Modern Slavery Innovation Fund","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, which organisations will receive funding under the Modern Slavery Innovation Fund round that concluded on 8 March 2017.","false","Biography information for Paul Blomfield","Sheffield Central","Paul Blomfield","69882"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715082","Home Office","false","2017-04-18","<p>The Office of the Immigration Services Commissioners’ (OISC) annual report and accounts sets out the number of complaints received by the OISC. Between March 2010 and April 2016, 569 complaints against regulated advisors were substantiated by the OISC.</p><p> </p><p>In the last 3 years (2014 - 2017) the Commissioner has received 403 separate complaints against regulated organisations which were subsequently substantiated. Of these:</p><p> </p><ul><li>Four people made two separate complaints each.</li><li>One person made three separate complaints.</li><li>The remaining complaints were submitted by an individual person or organisation.</li></ul>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-04-18T16:39:09.027Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715082/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715082/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715082/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-03-29","Immigration: Advisory Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many complaints have been substantiated by the Office of the Immigration Services Commissioner; and how many such complaints have been made by each individual complainant.","false","Biography information for Rosie Cooper","West Lancashire","Rosie Cooper","69904"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715083","Home Office","false","2017-04-18","<p>The Office of the Director of Labour Market Enforcement is jointly funded by the Home Office and the Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy. The forecast for 2017-18 is still in development so we have made notional provision to ensure that Director LME has the necessary funding to fulfil his role. We will set Director LME’s budget each year in line with a forecast submitted by the Director’s Office.</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton",,"2017-04-18T16:41:42.937Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715083/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715083/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715083/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-03-29","Director of Labour Market Enforcement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what operating budget has been set for the Office of the Director of Labour Market Enforcement in 2017-18 and each of the subsequent two years.","false","Biography information for Paul Blomfield","Sheffield Central","Paul Blomfield","69883"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715084","Home Office","false","2017-04-18","<p>The Director of Labour Market Enforcement has a statutory duty to co-operate with the Independent Anti-Slavery Commissioner, by virtue of section 43 of the Modern Slavery Act 2015 and Schedule 3 to that Act, as amended by the Modern Slavery Act 2015 (Duty to Co-operate with Commissioner) Regulations 2016.</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton",,"2017-04-18T16:42:14.287Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715084/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715084/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715084/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-03-29","Independent Anti-Slavery Commissioner and Director of Labour Market Enforcement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what the formal relationship is between the Independent Anti-Slavery Commissioner and the Director of Labour Market Enforcement.","false","Biography information for Paul Blomfield","Sheffield Central","Paul Blomfield","69884"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715085","Home Office","false","2017-04-18","<p>The Prime Minister was clear in her statement to Parliament on 29 March that we would seek to guarantee the rights of EU citizens already living in Britain, and the rights of British nationals in other member states, as early as we can. This is set out very clearly in the UK's Article 50 letter as an early priority for the talks ahead.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","69852","2017-04-18T15:34:03.877Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715085/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715085/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715085/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-03-29","Immigration: EEA Nationals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, if she will make provision for EU and EEA citizens living in the UK for a period exceeding five years and who have not yet exercised their treaty rights to obtain permanent residence before the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","69851"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715086","Home Office","false","2017-04-18","<p>The Prime Minister was clear in her statement to Parliament on 29 March that we would seek to guarantee the rights of EU citizens already living in Britain, and the rights of British nationals in other member states, as early as we can. This is set out very clearly in the UK's Article 50 letter as an early priority for the talks ahead.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","69851","2017-04-18T15:34:03.927Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715086/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715086/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715086/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-03-29","Immigration: EEA Nationals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, if she will make provision for EU and EEA citizens living in the UK who are married to UK nationals and who have not yet exercised their treaty rights to obtain permanent residence before the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","69852"
