ril 2010.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","69769"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715163","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-04-19","<p>Housing Benefit can continue to be paid on the grounds of low income if a claimant loses their entitlement to Jobseeker’s Allowance. Therefore, the Department has not undertaken any assessment of the effect of losing Jobseeker’s Allowance on Housing Benefit claimants.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2017-04-19T11:44:35.927Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715163/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715163/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715163/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-03-29","Jobseeker's Allowance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what assessment his Department has made of the effect on claimants of jobseeker's allowance who have their entitlement stopped and subsequently lose their entitlement to housing benefit.","false","Biography information for Kate Osamor","Edmonton","Kate Osamor","69796"
