verpool City Region","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many and what proportion of families in (a) Garston and Halewood constituency and (b) Liverpool City Region in receipt of child tax credits were households of two or more children in each year since April 2010.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","69790"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715193","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-04-18","<p>The information requested is not readily available and to provide it would incur disproportionate cost.</p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds",,"2017-04-18T15:12:25.447Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715193/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715193/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715193/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-03-29","Universal Credit: Liverpool City Region","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many and what proportion of people in (a) Garston and Halewood constituency and (b) Liverpool City Region in receipt of income-based jobseeker's allowance have claimed under the universal credit programme since that programme's introduction.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","69784"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715194","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-04-18","<p>People in Garston and Halewood Constituency and Liverpool Local Authority in receipt of a Universal Credit payment since April 2016:</p><p> </p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong> </strong></p></td><td><p>Number of UC recipients</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Garston and Halewood Constituency</p></td><td><p>2,000*</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Liverpool Local Authority</p></td><td><p>11,000**</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p><em>Figures are rounded to the nearest hundred* or thousand** and based on December 2016 statistics.</em></p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds",,"2017-04-18T15:22:34.847Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715194/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715194/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715194/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-03-29","Universal Credit: Liverpool City Region","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many people in (a) Garston and Halewood constituency and (b) Liverpool City Region have been in receipt of universal credit since April 2016.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","69785"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715195","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-04-18","<p>Qualitative research into the limiting of backdating with Local Authority Housing Benefit Managers has been undertaken. This was published in January 2017.</p><p> </p><p>The full report is available here <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/584664/local-authority-insight-research-wave-32.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/584664/local-authority-insight-research-wave-32.pdf</a></p><p> </p><p>A quantitative survey is planned and the findings will be published in due course.</p><p> </p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2017-04-18T15:59:57.843Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715195/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715195/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715195/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-03-29","Housing Benefit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, if he will carry out an impact assessment on the restrictions to backdating housing benefit introduced in April 2016 for working-age claimants.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","69786"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715196","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-04-19","<p><strong></strong></p><p>The information requested for Liverpool Local Authorities is published and available for each month from November 2008 to February 2013 and can be found in Table 10 of the publications at:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/housing-benefit-and-council-tax-benefit-caseload-statistics--2" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/housing-benefit-and-council-tax-benefit-caseload-statistics--2</a></p><p> </p><p>Council Tax Benefit (CTB) was replaced in April 2013 by the Local Council Tax Reduction Scheme and in England the Department for Communities and Local Government is now responsible for these statistics. The Scottish and Welsh Governments have similar responsibility.</p><p> </p><p>The information requested for Garston and Halewood Parliamentary Constituency was not readily available during that period and could only be provided at disproportionate cost.</p><p> </p><p>However a Parliamentary Constituency breakdown for CTB was produced as a one-off exercise for January 2011 and this is published at:</p><p><a href="http://webarchive.nationalarchives.gov.uk/20130107093842/http:/statistics.dwp.gov.uk/asd/asd1/hb_ctb/hb_ctb_parlc_jan11.xls" target="_blank">http://webarchive.nationalarchives.gov.uk/20130107093842/http://statistics.dwp.gov.uk/asd/asd1/hb_ctb/hb_ctb_parlc_jan11.xls</a></p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2017-04-19T11:49:07.393Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715196/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715196/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/715196/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-03-29","Council Tax Benefits: Liverpool City Region","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many households in (a) Garston and Halewood constituency and (b) Liverpool City Region were in receipt of council tax benefit subject for each year from April 2010 until April 2013.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","69779"
