"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714566","Department of Health","false","2017-04-04","<p>We are aware of a number of recent developments regarding robotic arms and prosthetics, however all of these procedures remain at a relatively early stage and more scientific trials would be needed to demonstrate their efficacy and safety before being considered for routine National Health Service use.</p>","Warrington South","David Mowat",,"2017-04-04T13:07:05.033Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714566/answer","Biography information for David Mowat","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714566/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714566/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-03-28","Orthopaedics: Robotics","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what assessment he has made of making available robotic arms on the NHS for people with limb amputations.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","69407"
